      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUSH MAYHEM (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when sixth at Shepparton over 390m behind Ring (22.75) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Rates on top in this line up. SHE REBEL (7) finds it hard to win. Finished third (22.63) at this track latest and might be close to finding winning form again. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to her name from nine starts. Will give a great sight again. ANALYZATION (3) boasts strong form at this course and distance having won three times from three starts. Below best last time at Ballarat (25.84) in a Grade 5 FIN, finishing a 9 length eighth. Suited here and expected to run well. HARA HACHI BU (6) finished in the placings last start and deserves some thought.",
